'''帐户认证'''（又称'''帐户验证'''，{{Lang-en|Account verification}}）是验证[[用户|帐户]]是否由指定的真实个人或组织拥有并运营的过程。[[社会化媒体|社交媒体]]网站等都提供帐户认证服务，他们通过在个人或组织名称旁边的[[勾號|勾号]]图标、“V”字标识或徽章，使人们通常可以从视觉上区分已认证的帐户。 

帐户认证可以提高在线服务的质量，减少[[马甲_(网络用语)|马甲]]、{{Le|社交媒体机器人|Social bot}}、[[網路白目|网络白目]]、[[濫發電子訊息|滥发电子信息]]、[[破壞|破坏]]行为、[[假新聞|假新闻]]、[[造谣|造谣]]和{{Le|别国干预选举|Foreign electoral intervention}}。

== 历史 ==
帐户认证最初是面向公众人物和具有公共利益的帐户的功能<ref>{{Cite web|title=About verified accounts|url=https://help.twitter.com/en/managing-your-account/about-twitter-verified-accounts|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2016-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719090643/https://support.twitter.com/groups/31-twitter-basics/topics/111-features/articles/119135-about-verified-accounts|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由[[Twitter|Twitter]]在2009年6月引入<ref name="twitter1">{{Cite web|title=Not Playing Ball|url=https://blog.twitter.com/official/en_us/a/2009/not-playing-ball.html|author=Stone|date=2009-06-06|first=Biz|work=Twitter|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427151225/https://blog.twitter.com/official/en_us/a/2009/not-playing-ball.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="twitter2">{{Cite news|author=Kanalley|first=Craig|title=Why Twitter Verifies Users: The History Behind the Blue Checkmark|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/craig-kanalley/twitter-verified-accounts_b_2863282.html|accessdate=2014-06-09|work=Huffington Post|date=2013-03-12|archive-date=2018-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927015328/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/craig-kanalley/twitter-verified-accounts_b_2863282.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="twitter3">{{Cite web|title=Twitter Launches Verified Accounts|url=http://mashable.com/2009/06/11/twitter-verified-accounts-2/|author=Cashmore|first=Pete|publisher=|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416180545/https://mashable.com/2009/06/11/twitter-verified-accounts-2/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2011年，[[Google+|Google+]]推出类似功能<ref name="google1">{{Cite web|title=Google+ now verifying accounts of the famous|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/social-media/google-now-verifying-accounts-of-the-famous/|date=2011-08-21|publisher=|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327102025/https://www.digitaltrends.com/social-media/google-now-verifying-accounts-of-the-famous/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[Facebook|Facebook]]在2012年推出<ref name="facebook1">{{Cite web|title=Facebook Launches Verified Accounts and Pseudonyms|url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/02/15/facebook-verified-accounts-alternate-names/|author=Constine|first=Josh|publisher=|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2012-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120216152816/http://techcrunch.com/2012/02/15/facebook-verified-accounts-alternate-names/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[Instagram|Instagram]]在2014年推出<ref name="instagram1">{{Cite web|title=Instagram Is Introducing 'Verified Badges' For Public Figures|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/instagram-verified-badges-2014-12|publisher=|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323175818/https://www.businessinsider.com/instagram-verified-badges-2014-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[Pinterest|Pinterest]]在2015年推出。<ref name="pinterest1">{{Cite web|title=Pinterest is introducing verified accounts for public figures|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/pinterest-is-introducing-verified-accounts-for-public-figures-brands-celebrities-2015-6|publisher=|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191026212819/https://www.businessinsider.com/pinterest-is-introducing-verified-accounts-for-public-figures-brands-celebrities-2015-6|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[YouTube|YouTube]]上，用户获得100,000以上个订阅后，便可以提交认证徽章的请求。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verification badges on channels - YouTube Help|url=https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/3046484?hl=en|accessdate=2019-02-08|work=support.google.com|archive-date=2019-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828135816/https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/3046484?hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>它还为音乐家和乐队提供了“官方艺术家”（{{Lang|en|official artist}}）徽章。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Introduction to Official Artist Channels - YouTube Help|url=https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/7336634?hl=en|accessdate=2019-02-08|work=support.google.com|archive-date=2019-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222042656/https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/7336634?hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在中国大陆，[[新浪微博|新浪微博]]、[[腾讯微博|腾讯微博]]等[[微博|微博]]服务率先推出认证<ref>{{Cite web|title=微博认证|url=https://verified.weibo.com/|accessdate=2020-07-18|author=|date=|format=|publisher=新浪微博|language=|archive-date=2017-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170717032317/http://verified.weibo.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=微博认证不再想认就能认——新浪微博首次公布个人认证流程，必须提供单位证明  新政实行后，因审核严格，认证拒绝率高达70%以上|author=|date=2013-09-06|work=潍坊晚报|publisher=|accessdate=|language=|format=}}</ref>。为了确保名人的身份属实，获得用户的信任，各大微博平台都开始实行认证功能。在微博上，一些社会知名人士或者机构的用户名后面有一个字母“V”或一个对勾，标志下面还会标明用户的社会身份。微博认证意味着该用户经过微博平台的审核，证明其身份属实。在新浪微博，个人认证完全免费，不需要收费。<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=|title=谁来规范微博认证？|author=|date=2011-11-17|work=北方新报|publisher=|accessdate=|language=|format=}}</ref>但微博认证在[[郭美美事件|郭美美事件]]中引发巨大争议<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=微博认证“变味儿”了——“郭美美事件”曝微博乱象 身份认证成敛财工具|author=|date=2011-06-25|work=北京晨报|publisher=|accessdate=|language=|format=}}</ref>，微博认证也成为网络敛财工具，一些人在网上兜售微博认证<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=微博认证加“V” 花钱一切OK——记者调查发现：网上兜售认证敛财 营销乱象已踩到法律红线|author=|date=2011-06-25|work=兰州晨报|publisher=|accessdate=|language=|format=}}</ref>。 

2016年7月，[[Twitter|Twitter]]宣布，除了公众人物外，任何人也都可以申请帐户认证。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Twitter Lets Anyone Apply for a Blue 'Verified' Badge|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/twitter-lets-anyone-apply-for-a-blue-verified-badge-1468960671|author=Olivarez-Giles|date=2016-07-19|first=Nathan|publisher=|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2018-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830210203/https://www.wsj.com/articles/twitter-lets-anyone-apply-for-a-blue-verified-badge-1468960671|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Blue ticks for all: Twitter allows users to apply to be verified|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2016/jul/19/blue-ticks-for-all-twitter-allows-all-users-to-be-verified|author=Association|date=2016-07-19|first=Press|publisher=|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414061811/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2016/jul/19/blue-ticks-for-all-twitter-allows-all-users-to-be-verified|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年2月，这一活动被Twitter暂停，此前，白人[[民族主义|民族主义]]者、[[2017年团结右翼集会|2017年团结右翼集会]]组织者之一{{Le|贾森·凯斯勒|Jason Kessler}}的账户获得Twitter认证，引发了人们对其“可信性”和“重要性”的争议。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Roettgers|first=Janko|title=Twitter Pauses Verifications After Backlash Over Verifying Far-Right Extremist|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/twitter-verifications-suspended-1202610990/|accessdate=2019-04-05|work=[[Variety_(magazine)|Variety]]|date=2017-11-09|language=en|archive-date=2019-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816224342/https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/twitter-verifications-suspended-1202610990/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Twitter stops its verification program after giving its 'verified' badge to the organizer of the Charlottesville 'Unite the Right' rally|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/twitter-suspends-account-verifications-after-backlash-2017-11|author=Cakebread|date=2017-11-09|first=Caroline|publisher=|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001123626/https://www.businessinsider.com/twitter-suspends-account-verifications-after-backlash-2017-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年3月，在{{Le|Periscope|Periscope_(app)}}的直播中，Twitter的联合创始人兼首席执行官[[杰克·多西|杰克·多西]]讨论了允许任何个人获得经过认证的帐户的想法<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/twitter-verified-account-open-everyone-1202722587/|title=Twitter CEO Wants to Open Up Verified Accounts to Everyone|author=Spangler|first=Todd|work=Variety|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427150515/https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/twitter-verified-account-open-everyone-1202722587/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Instagram自2018年8月起开始允许用户请求认证。<ref>{{Cite web|title=You can now apply to be verified in Instagram|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/8/28/17791450/instagram-verified-request-verification-status|accessdate=2018-09-26|author=Liao|date=2018-08-28|first=Shannon|work=The Verge|archive-date=2018-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019180534/https://www.theverge.com/2018/8/28/17791450/instagram-verified-request-verification-status|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

2018年4月，[[Facebook|Facebook]]联合创始人兼首席执行官[[马克·扎克伯格|马克·扎克伯格]]宣布，将要求购买政治性或基于社会重大议题的广告的人，认证其身份和所在位置。<ref name="zuck2018">{{Cite web|title=Mark Zuckerberg - With important elections coming up in...|url=https://www.facebook.com/zuck/posts/10104784125525891|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201008201511/https://www.facebook.com/zuck/posts/10104784125525891|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/06/business/facebook-verification-ads.html|title=Facebook to Require Verified Identities for Future Political Ads|work=The New York Times|date=2018-04-06|author=Nicas|first=Jack|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225084907/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/06/business/facebook-verification-ads.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他还表示，Facebook将要求管理大页面的个人进行认证。2018年5月，[[Google|谷歌]]高级副总裁[[肯特·沃克|肯特·沃克]]宣布，在美国购买有政治倾向广告的人需要认证其身份。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Supporting election integrity through greater advertising transparency|url=https://www.blog.google/topics/public-policy/supporting-election-integrity-through-greater-advertising-transparency/|date=2018-05-04|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109023545/https://www.blog.google/topics/public-policy/supporting-election-integrity-through-greater-advertising-transparency/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 方式与技术 ==
帐户认证有多种方式。{{Le|身份验证服务|Identity verification service}}是第三方的解决方案，可用于确保一个人提供与真实人的身份相关的信息。此类服务可能会验证诸如[[駕駛執照|驾驶执照]]或[[护照|护照之]]类的[[身分證|身份证明文件]]的真实性（称为文件证明，{{Lang|en|documentary verification}}），或者可能会通过诸如{{Le|征信机构|Credit bureau}}或政府数据之类的权威来源来验证身份信息，这称为非文件证明。<ref>{{cite web|title=The case for digital IDs|url=https://www.techuk.org/images/documents/digital_id_FINAL_WEBSITE.pdf|date=2019-02-01|last=|first=|website=TechUK|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107234406/https://www.techuk.org/images/documents/digital_id_FINAL_WEBSITE.pdf|archive-date=2020-11-07|access-date=2019-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>而身份证件验证，即让用户上传扫描或拍摄[[身分證|身份证件]]也是一种正在使用的做法，例如[[Facebook|Facebook]]会使用这一方法<ref name="facebook_hc">{{Cite web|title=Facebook Help Center: Confirm Your Identity with Facebook § Submitting ID|url=https://www.facebook.com/help/contact/183000765122339|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322014130/https://www.facebook.com/help/contact/183000765122339|dead-url=no}}</ref>。据称，当需要用户显示账号的所有权或确认他们的名字时，他们将接受此类认证<ref name="facebook_hc" />。在2018年1月，[[Facebook|Facebook]]购买了Confirm.io，这是一家正在推进认证身份文件真实性的技术的初创公司<ref>{{Cite web|title=Facebook Acquires Biometric ID Verification Startup Confirm.io|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/01/23/facebook-confirm-io/|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808232705/https://techcrunch.com/2018/01/23/facebook-confirm-io/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

此外，还有行为验证、银行账户验证、[[多重要素驗證|多因素验证]]等多种认证方法。多个服务提供商使用的帐户认证过程有时也可以相互佐证。{{Le|OpenID Connect|OpenID Connect}}包含一个用户信息协议，该协议可用于链接多个帐户，从而确认用户信息。<ref>{{Cite web|title=OpenID Connect 1.0|url=https://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html#UserInfo|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812201006/https://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html#UserInfo|dead-url=no}}</ref>

